  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SLGP SIB SME RSF II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Increased access to finance for SMEs: The project is expected to increase access to longer term financing for SMEs in Cote d&apos;Ivoire.
- Inclusiveness: Inclusive growth is expected to be achieved through the successful banking of currently unserved/underserved SMEs (such as women SMEs, agribusiness value chains, smaller size SMEs).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is part of IFCs Small Loan Guarantee Program (SLGP or Program) which provides risk sharing instrument to client banks looking to expand SME lending in underserved markets. SLGP is supported by the IDA18 IFC-MIGA Private Sector Window Blended Finance Facility (IDA PSW-BFF), which was created by the Word Bank Group to catalyze private sector investment in IDA countries, with a focus on fragile and conflict-affected states. The IDA PSW BFF support would enable IFC to rapidly roll out a program of risk sharing facilities to reach segments facing serious market failures in IDA countries and provide access to finance to such underserved targeted market segments which IFC could not otherwise serve due to the associated high risk.&#xA0;The concessional support from IDA PSW, will, therefore, enable SIB to expand lending to SMEs including small agribusinesses in Cote dIvoire with inadequate or no collateral or weak cash flow but with potential to grow their business initiatives.</narrative>
  </description>
